					<span class="comment-middot">&middot;</span>
					<span class="comment-time">9:33 pm</span>
				</a>
			</span>
		</div>
		<div class="comment-content" style="display:block;">

			<p>I do not believe that minimum wage should be higher than $8/hour. The amount of money one makes on minimum wage is enough just to get by. Such jobs at Popeye&#8217;s or McDonalds are not jobs that require much skill. Teens are usually hired at these places. If minimum wage is increased, people will lack the motivation for education because they are working a job that pays a good enough amount that they won&#8217;t need a higher education to earn a higher wage. Not only that, but increasing minimum wage will affect the employers and the company. The employers will have to lessen the amount of employees, which can result in a loss of jobs, therefore making situations worse. The prices at these companies will also increase if more money is needed to pay employees, which will result in dissatisfaction and a loss of customers.</p>

		</div>
	</div><!-- #comment-## -->
